[Opini]
Islam di dunia. Ada apa dengan dunia ini?  Ada apa dengan Indonesia ku ini. Saya sebagai anak muda masih belum begitu paham apa yang benar dan apa yang salah. Masih belom sadar mana yang hasan dan yang zholim. Saya menerima informasi yang berbeda, ya terdapat dua sisi. Dan saya terlalu sering mendapat informasi yang bisa dibilang condong ke sayap kanan. Misalnya,  menolak RUU PKS, menolak bahwa bendera hitam itu tidak berarti orang HTI,  setuju bahwa orang islam saat ini sedang  uji.  Seperti di India, bahkan di negara Indonesia ini yang mayoritas orang islam. Mendengar cerita masyarakat muslim terlebih lg muslimah di Ughyur yang menyesakkan dada,  dan takut akan menimpa di Indonesia. Dunia berubah tiap harinya.  Tiap berganti program atau kebijakan,  suara pemimpin dan orang-orang diatas didengar,  tanpa mendengar jeritan orang-orang dibawah.  Pentingkah suara kami sebenarnya? Seperti itu,  hanya contoh.

Rumeli Hisar, Fatih Sultan Mehmedin stanbulun Fethi iin yaptrd ve askeri dehasn gsteren bir eserdir. Rumeli Hisarnn projesini Fatih Sultan Mehmed bizzat kendisi hazrlamtr. Hisarn yapmna 15 Nisan 1452 ylnda balanm ve ayn yl 31 Austosta tamamlanmtr. Yapm ok ksa srede tamamlanan bu hisar ile Fatih, stanbulu almak istediini aslnda herkese apak ilan etmitir.

Rumeli Castle (Rumeli Hisar) is an Ottoman fortress dating to 1452. It was built by Ottoman sultan Mehmed II (Mehmed the Conqueror) in preparation of the conquest of Constantinople. The castle is situated on the shore of the Bosphorus Strait at its narrowest point with approximately 660 meters.

SpiceBazaar was built in 1664, as part of the Yeni Camii complex. It is a beautiful place with wide range of spices. It is one of the most famous Bazaar in Istanbul. It has win the prize for the most colorful, fragrant, and the most fun bazar. Aside from the spices, there are also many types of tea as a rosebud, jasmine, and fruit, Turkish delight in every color and flavor, herbal remedies, but also dried fruits as an apricots, figs, dates and even strawberries and kiwis. You can also buy honey, baklava, olive oil soaps, Turkish coffee and much more from Spice Bazaar.
